BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 746.00 Td (  capture, FPGA formatting and packetization, Ethernet transport, and host-side Holoscan processing.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 724.40 Td (Technical details to emphasize) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 700.60 Td (- The FPGA is not only a pass-through device.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 689.80 Td (- It terminates sensor protocols, formats data, and packetizes it.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 679.00 Td (- The NVIDIA host receives the stream and runs Holoscan operators.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 668.20 Td (- 25G is important because modern sensors and multi-camera systems exceed simple 1G/10G bandwidth limits.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 646.60 Td (Transition) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 622.80 Td (> I will start with Holoscan concepts, then show how the FPGA IP and Altera reference designs fit into that) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 612.00 Td (  model.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 590.40 Td (----------------------------------------------------------------------------------) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 568.80 Td (Slide 2 - Agenda) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 542.00 Td (Purpose of the slide) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 518.20 Td (Set expectations for the flow of the session.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 496.60 Td (What to say) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 472.80 Td (> The agenda starts with concepts: Holoscan, Holoscan Sensor Bridge, and FPGA-based sensor-to-Ethernet) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 462.00 Td (  conversion. Then I will cover the market relevance, available reference designs, how to select the right) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 451.20 Td (  design, and finally the demo setup, hardware architecture, software flow, and bring-up observations.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 429.60 Td (Technical details to emphasize) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 405.80 Td (- The audience should expect both architecture and practical bring-up details.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 395.00 Td (- The later slides include hardware and software internals, not only demo commands.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 373.40 Td (Suggested pacing) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 349.60 Td (- Slides 3-5: concept and value proposition.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 338.80 Td (- Slides 6-11: market and design discovery.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 328.00 Td (- Slides 12-17: demo setup.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 317.20 Td (- Slides 18-27: FPGA architecture and transport.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 306.40 Td (- Slides 28-31: software, app flow, and platform caveats.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 284.80 Td (----------------------------------------------------------------------------------) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 263.20 Td (Slide 3 - Holoscan Overview) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 236.40 Td (Purpose of the slide) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 212.60 Td (Explain the Holoscan programming model: applications, fragments, operators, and data flow.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 191.00 Td (What to say) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 167.20 Td (> Holoscan is NVIDIA's framework for building low-latency streaming AI pipelines. A Holoscan application is) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 156.40 Td (  composed of fragments. A fragment contains a graph of operators, and each operator performs a unit of work.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 145.60 Td (  Operators receive streaming inputs, process data, and publish outputs to the next operator.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 124.00 Td (Explain the terms) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 100.20 Td (- Application: complete pipeline.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 89.40 Td (- Fragment: partition of the application, possibly deployable across systems.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 78.60 Td (- Operator: computational or IO block.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 67.80 Td (- Source operator: introduces data into the graph.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 57.00 Td (- Sink operator: consumes or displays data.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 500 26 Td (Page 2 of 19) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
