BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 735.20 Td (Tie to this demo) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 711.40 Td (> In this demo, the Holoscan Sensor Bridge receiver is effectively the source operator. It receives camera) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 700.60 Td (  frames from the FPGA. The image-processing, demosaic, format conversion, and inference blocks are processing) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 689.80 Td (  operators. Holoviz is the visualization sink.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 668.20 Td (Technical emphasis) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 644.40 Td (- This graph abstraction is useful for real-time sensor systems.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 633.60 Td (- It separates ingest, preprocessing, inference, and visualization.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 622.80 Td (- It allows the FPGA transport layer to be integrated into a GPU processing pipeline.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 601.20 Td (Likely audience question) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 577.40 Td (Q: Is Holoscan only for medical?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 555.80 Td (A: No. Holoscan originated strongly in medical and edge AI use cases, but the framework applies to any) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 545.00 Td (  streaming sensor pipeline: robotics, industrial vision, broadcast, wireless, aerospace, and defense.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 523.40 Td (----------------------------------------------------------------------------------) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 501.80 Td (Slide 4 - Holoscan Sensor Bridge IP) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 475.00 Td (Purpose of the slide) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 451.20 Td (Explain what the HSB IP does in the FPGA and how it interacts with host software.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 429.60 Td (What to say) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 405.80 Td (> Holoscan Sensor Bridge has an FPGA IP component and a host software component. The FPGA IP provides both a) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 395.00 Td (  control plane and a data transport plane. The control plane gives host software access to HSB registers,) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 384.20 Td (  external IP registers over APB, and sensor interfaces such as I2C or SPI. The data plane moves frames between) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 373.40 Td (  FPGA and host over high-speed Ethernet.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 351.80 Td (Key technical points) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 328.00 Td (- HSB IP is open-source NVIDIA FPGA IP under Apache 2.0.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 317.20 Td (- It provides internal registers and external control interfaces.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 306.40 Td (- It can control sensors through interfaces such as I2C/SPI.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 295.60 Td (- It packetizes frame data for Ethernet transport.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 284.80 Td (- It presents data to Holoscan through CPU or GPU memory.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 263.20 Td (RoCE versus CoE) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 239.40 Td (> On platforms with ConnectX, HSB can use RoCEv2. AGX Thor does not use RoCEv2 for this path. Thor uses Camera) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 228.60 Td (  over Ethernet, or CoE, which is RDMA-like for receive acceleration.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 207.00 Td (Important nuance) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 183.20 Td (- CoE is receive-side acceleration only.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 172.40 Td (- It is not identical to RoCEv2.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 161.60 Td (- The FPGA packet format must match the host driver expectation.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 140.00 Td (Likely audience question) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 116.20 Td (Q: Can the same HSB IP support both Linux socket and accelerated paths?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 94.60 Td (A: Yes, but the FPGA and host configuration must match the chosen transport. Linux socket mode is simpler and) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 83.80 Td (  useful for debug. CoE/RoCE paths are used for higher performance.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 62.20 Td (----------------------------------------------------------------------------------) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 500 26 Td (Page 3 of 19) Tj ET
endstream
