BT /F2 13 Tf 50 735.20 Td (Slide 5 - Altera FPGA-based Sensor-to-Ethernet Converters) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 708.40 Td (Purpose of the slide) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 684.60 Td (Position Altera FPGAs as flexible sensor-ingest and Ethernet conversion devices.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 663.00 Td (What to say) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 639.20 Td (> Altera FPGAs enable sensor-to-Ethernet conversion at the edge. Many sensors do not connect directly to GPU) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 628.40 Td (  platforms. They use interfaces like MIPI CSI, JESD204, LVDS, SLVS-EC, SDI, SPI, I2C, or custom GPIO. The FPGA) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 617.60 Td (  terminates these protocols, optionally preprocesses or synchronizes data, and sends it over Ethernet to GPU or) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 606.80 Td (  CPU compute.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 585.20 Td (Value proposition) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 561.40 Td (- Ultra-low latency ingest.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 550.60 Td (- Protocol flexibility.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 539.80 Td (- Deterministic timing.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 529.00 Td (- Bandwidth scaling from 10G to 25G, 100G, and beyond.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 518.20 Td (- Offload preprocessing before the host.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 507.40 Td (- Reduces system integration complexity.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 485.80 Td (Strong phrase to use) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 462.00 Td (> The FPGA solves the hard real-time sensor and transport problem; Holoscan solves the host-side GPU processing) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 451.20 Td (  and AI workflow.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 429.60 Td (Technical audience angle) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 405.80 Td (- Mention that Ethernet decouples sensor location from host location.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 395.00 Td (- FPGAs can aggregate, timestamp, packetize, and align streams before the host sees them.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 384.20 Td (- Customers can customize the FPGA for proprietary sensors or custom preprocessing.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 362.60 Td (----------------------------------------------------------------------------------) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 341.00 Td (Slide 6 - Markets / Use Cases) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 314.20 Td (Purpose of the slide) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 290.40 Td (Show that this architecture applies broadly.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 268.80 Td (What to say) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 245.00 Td (> The architecture is relevant wherever high-rate sensor data needs deterministic capture and GPU-side) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 234.20 Td (  processing. Examples include robotics, industrial inspection, medical imaging, studio production, wireless, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 223.40 Td (  defense.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 201.80 Td (Market-by-market talk track) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 178.00 Td (Robotics:) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 156.40 Td (- Multi-camera, lidar, radar, IMU, and actuator feedback.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 145.60 Td (- Need timestamping, synchronization, low latency, and sensor fusion.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 134.80 Td (- FPGA handles deterministic ingest; Holoscan handles perception and AI.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 113.20 Td (Industrial:) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 91.60 Td (- Machine vision, defect inspection, thermal imaging, vibration monitoring.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 80.80 Td (- FPGA handles triggering, deterministic capture, and transport.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 70.00 Td (- Host runs classification, measurement, and visualization.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 500 26 Td (Page 4 of 19) Tj ET
endstream
