stream
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 746.00 Td (   Instantiates NVIDIA HSB IP, exposes SIFs, APB control, I2C, and host interface.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 724.40 Td (4. Ethernet subsystem:) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 713.60 Td (   Instantiates hardened Ethernet IP and supporting PHY/reset logic.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 692.00 Td (Important statement) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 668.20 Td (> Control and data both move over Ethernet. The same network path is used for discovery, register access,) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 657.40 Td (  camera configuration, and frame transport.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 635.80 Td (----------------------------------------------------------------------------------) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 614.20 Td (Slide 21 - Video Interface) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 587.40 Td (Purpose of the slide) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 563.60 Td (Explain how video is represented before HSB.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 542.00 Td (What to say) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 518.20 Td (> The video interface is responsible for taking raw camera data from MIPI and converting it into the packed CSI) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 507.40 Td (  format expected by the HSB host software.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 485.80 Td (Technical details) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 462.00 Td (- MIPI D-PHY supports two 4-lane receive interfaces.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 451.20 Td (- CSI-2 receiver supports RAW10 and RAW12.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 440.40 Td (- IMX678 does not support RAW8 in this demo path.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 429.60 Td (- ASVP carries four pixels in parallel.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 418.80 Td (- RAW10 wastes bits in ASVP representation.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 408.00 Td (- CSI packing removes that inefficiency.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 386.40 Td (Why packing matters) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 362.60 Td (> The host receiver expects line lengths and pixel packing to match the sensor mode. If the FPGA packing and) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 351.80 Td (  software mode disagree, frames appear corrupted or fail downstream.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 330.20 Td (----------------------------------------------------------------------------------) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 308.60 Td (Slide 22 - HSB Subsystem) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 281.80 Td (Purpose of the slide) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 258.00 Td (Explain HSB IP integration.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 236.40 Td (What to say) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 212.60 Td (> The HSB subsystem instantiates NVIDIA HSB IP and the support logic needed to connect it to Altera video and) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 201.80 Td (  Ethernet blocks.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 180.20 Td (Technical details) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 156.40 Td (- SIF inputs receive packed video streams.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 145.60 Td (- APB buses expose control registers.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 134.80 Td (- I2C peripheral path supports camera control.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 124.00 Td (- AVST/AXIS shims adapt interface conventions.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 113.20 Td (- System ID provides build identification.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 91.60 Td (Important nuance) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 67.80 Td (> The shims are not doing image processing. They adapt bus protocol, byte ordering, and streaming signal) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 57.00 Td (  conventions between Altera and NVIDIA blocks.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 500 26 Td (Page 11 of 19) Tj ET
endstream
