BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 735.20 Td (----------------------------------------------------------------------------------) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 713.60 Td (Slide 23 - 10GbE Design vs 25GbE Design) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 686.80 Td (Purpose of the slide) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 663.00 Td (Compare design tradeoffs.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 641.40 Td (What to say) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 617.60 Td (> The 10G design is a simpler two-stream pipeline. The 25G design supports replicated streams and up to eight) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 606.80 Td (  SIF paths, which is useful for bandwidth and multiviewer demonstrations.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 585.20 Td (Technical differences) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 561.40 Td (10G:) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 539.80 Td (- Two video streams.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 529.00 Td (- Separate FIFOs.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 518.20 Td (- Simpler resource profile.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 507.40 Td (- Good for stable first demo.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 485.80 Td (25G:) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 464.20 Td (- Streams replicated and presented to eight HSB SIFs.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 453.40 Td (- FIFOs incorporated into broadcaster IP.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 442.60 Td (- Higher bandwidth.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 431.80 Td (- More logic due to CoE packetizer support.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 410.20 Td (Customer guidance) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 386.40 Td (> Start with 10G for basic bring-up. Use 25G when demonstrating bandwidth, CoE, or multi-stream capability.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 364.80 Td (----------------------------------------------------------------------------------) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 343.20 Td (Slide 24 - HSB Parameters) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 316.40 Td (Purpose of the slide) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 292.60 Td (Point to NVIDIA HSB integration documentation.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 271.00 Td (What to say) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 247.20 Td (> HSB behavior is controlled by integration parameters. These define interface widths, enabled buses, SIF) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 236.40 Td (  configuration, packetization behavior, and peripheral options.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 214.80 Td (Why it matters) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 191.00 Td (- FPGA configuration and host software must match.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 180.20 Td (- Packetizer settings matter for CoE.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 169.40 Td (- SIF count and width affect resource use and stream mapping.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 158.60 Td (- Incorrect parameters can cause link-level success but application-level failure.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 137.00 Td (----------------------------------------------------------------------------------) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 115.40 Td (Slide 25 - HSB Wrapper Parameterization) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 88.60 Td (Purpose of the slide) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 64.80 Td (Explain Altera's wrapper value.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 500 26 Td (Page 12 of 19) Tj ET
