stream
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 735.20 Td (What to say) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 711.40 Td (> Altera created a Platform Designer component and wrapper around NVIDIA HSB IP to make integration easier and) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 700.60 Td (  less error-prone.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 679.00 Td (Technical capabilities) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 655.20 Td (- Exposes HSB parameters in GUI.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 644.40 Td (- Generates HOLOLINK_def.svh.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 633.60 Td (- Generates wrapper ports.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 622.80 Td (- Handles mixed SIF widths.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 612.00 Td (- Ties off unused signals.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 601.20 Td (- Supports register initialization.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 590.40 Td (- Keeps SPI0 visible when software expects it.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 579.60 Td (- Supports build revision and enumeration settings.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 558.00 Td (Customer value) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 534.20 Td (> This helps customers adapt HSB without hand-editing low-level macro files and wrapper logic.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 512.60 Td (----------------------------------------------------------------------------------) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 491.00 Td (Slide 26 - Resource Utilization) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 464.20 Td (Purpose of the slide) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 440.40 Td (Explain 25G resource cost.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 418.80 Td (What to say) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 395.00 Td (> The 25G design uses more FPGA resources because CoE packetizer support is enabled across multiple video SIFs.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 373.40 Td (Important number) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 349.60 Td (> The packetizer configuration adds approximately 7k ALMs per SIF. With eight SIFs, this becomes a significant) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 338.80 Td (  resource increase.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 317.20 Td (Technical tradeoff) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 293.40 Td (- CoE support improves host receive path.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 282.60 Td (- Multi-SIF support improves stream scaling.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 271.80 Td (- Both increase resource usage.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 250.20 Td (Customer guidance) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 226.40 Td (> If the customer does not need CoE or eight SIFs, there may be opportunities to reduce resource use in a) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 215.60 Td (  custom derivative.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 194.00 Td (----------------------------------------------------------------------------------) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 172.40 Td (Slide 27 - Camera Over Ethernet on Thor) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 145.60 Td (Purpose of the slide) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 121.80 Td (Explain Thor-specific transport.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 100.20 Td (What to say) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 76.40 Td (> AGX Thor does not use RoCEv2 in this path. It uses Camera over Ethernet, or CoE. CoE is RDMA-like for receive) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 65.60 Td (  acceleration but has different driver and packetization requirements.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 500 26 Td (Page 13 of 19) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
