BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 735.20 Td (Switch to 25G:) Tj ET
BT /F3 7.5 Tf 50 713.60 Td (sudo nvbootctrl set-active-boot-slot 0) Tj ET
BT /F3 7.5 Tf 50 704.50 Td (sudo reboot) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 684.60 Td (Switch to 10G:) Tj ET
BT /F3 7.5 Tf 50 663.00 Td (sudo nvbootctrl set-active-boot-slot 1) Tj ET
BT /F3 7.5 Tf 50 653.90 Td (sudo reboot) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 634.00 Td (Check:) Tj ET
BT /F3 7.5 Tf 50 612.40 Td (sudo nvbootctrl get-current-slot) Tj ET
BT /F3 7.5 Tf 50 603.30 Td (cat /sys/devices/platform/bus@0/*/net/mgbe*/speed) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 583.40 Td (Key message) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 559.60 Td (> This is not an nmcli setting. It is a boot configuration mode.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 538.00 Td (----------------------------------------------------------------------------------) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 516.40 Td (Slide 32 - Closing) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 489.60 Td (Purpose of the slide) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 465.80 Td (End with key customer takeaways.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 444.20 Td (What to say) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 420.40 Td (> In summary, we validated an end-to-end path from MIPI cameras through Agilex 5, over Ethernet, into NVIDIA) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 409.60 Td (  Holoscan on AGX Thor. The FPGA provides deterministic sensor ingest and transport, while Holoscan provides GPU) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 398.80 Td (  processing, visualization, and AI.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.5 Tf 50 377.20 Td (Final takeaways) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 353.40 Td (- 10G path is stable and recommended for first customer evaluation.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 342.60 Td (- 25G path works on AGX Thor after boot-slot switching.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 331.80 Td (- CoE repeated-run workaround is documented.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 321.00 Td (- MAX10 firmware update may be required on early MDKs.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 310.20 Td (- AI demos are possible once camera and transport are validated.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 288.60 Td (----------------------------------------------------------------------------------) Tj ET
BT /F2 18 Tf 50 267.00 Td (Expanded Technical Q&A) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 234.20 Td (Q1. Why do we need an FPGA in this architecture?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 207.40 Td (Because many sensors do not connect directly to NVIDIA GPU platforms in the required format, timing, or) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 196.60 Td (  bandwidth. The FPGA can terminate MIPI, JESD204, SLVS-EC, LVDS, SDI, SPI, I2C, GPIO, or custom protocols, then) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 185.80 Td (  synchronize, preprocess, packetize, and transport the data over Ethernet.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 164.20 Td (Q2. What is the exact division of work between FPGA and Holoscan?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 137.40 Td (The FPGA handles deterministic IO, sensor protocol adaptation, timing, packetization, and Ethernet transport.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 126.60 Td (  Holoscan handles host-side graph execution, GPU processing, image conversion, inference, visualization, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 115.80 Td (  application logic.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 94.20 Td (Q3. What does HSB IP provide?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 67.40 Td (HSB IP provides a host-accessible control plane and a high-speed data transport path. It exposes registers,) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 500 26 Td (Page 16 of 19) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
37 0 obj
<< /Type /Page /Parent 2 0 R /MediaBox [0 0 612 792] /Resources << /Font << /F1 3 0 R /F2 4 0 R /F3 5 0 R >> >> /Contents 36 0 R >>
endobj
38 0 obj
<< /Length 3856 >>
stream
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 746.00 Td (  sensor control interfaces, SIF data inputs, and Ethernet transport integration so host software can discover,) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 735.20 Td (  configure, and receive data from the FPGA.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 713.60 Td (Q4. What is a SIF?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 686.80 Td (SIF means Sensor Interface. It is a data input path into the HSB IP. The 25G design presents multiple video) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 676.00 Td (  streams to multiple SIFs, enabling multi-stream or replicated-stream operation.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 654.40 Td (Q5. What is the difference between Linux receiver, RoCE, and CoE?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 627.60 Td (Linux receiver uses the standard Linux network stack and is simpler but less accelerated. RoCE uses RDMA over) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 616.80 Td (  Converged Ethernet and is supported on platforms with appropriate NICs such as ConnectX. CoE is Thor's Camera-) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 606.00 Td (  over-Ethernet receive acceleration path and is RDMA-like on RX, but not the same as RoCE.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 584.40 Td (Q6. Why does Thor need boot-slot switching for 10G and 25G?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 557.60 Td (AGX Thor does not dynamically switch MGBE between 10GbE x4 and 25GbE x4 from Linux networking tools. The mode) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 546.80 Td (  is configured in the boot image/QSPI configuration. Capsule-based slot switching lets us move between modes by) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 536.00 Td (  selecting the active boot slot and rebooting.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 514.40 Td (Q7. What is the current boot-slot mapping?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 487.60 Td (From this bring-up:) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 466.00 Td (- Slot 0 = 25G.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 455.20 Td (- Slot 1 = 10G.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 433.60 Td (This should always be verified on the actual unit with nvbootctrl and MGBE speed checks.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 412.00 Td (Q8. How do we verify Thor is in 25G mode?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 385.20 Td (Run:) Tj ET
BT /F3 7.5 Tf 50 363.60 Td (cat /sys/devices/platform/bus@0/*/net/mgbe*/speed) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 343.70 Td (For 25G, expect 25000 for the MGBE ports. Then use ethtool to verify the connected port reports Speed:) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 332.90 Td (  25000Mb/s and Link detected: yes.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 311.30 Td (Q9. Why did the initial 25G link fail?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 284.50 Td (Thor was still booted in default 10G mode. The 25G FPGA image cannot link correctly when Thor MGBE is) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 273.70 Td (  configured for 10G. After switching Thor to 25G boot configuration, the link came up.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 252.10 Td (Q10. Why did camera I2C fail even though HSB enumeration worked?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 225.30 Td (HSB enumeration proves the Ethernet and FPGA HSB endpoint are reachable. Camera I2C is a separate path through) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 214.50 Td (  the FPGA to the sensor. On early MDK boards, MAX10 firmware did not power the MIPI connectors, so the cameras) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 203.70 Td (  could not respond to I2C.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 182.10 Td (Q11. How was the camera I2C issue fixed?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 155.30 Td (MAX10 was reflashed with the fixed image max10_top_rtl_v1p1p6_fw_v2p0p1.pof. SW4 was used to put MAX10 onto the) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 144.50 Td (  JTAG chain, then returned to OFF so the FPGA appears on the JTAG chain again.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 122.90 Td (Q12. Is the MAX10 issue expected for customer boards?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 96.10 Td (Customer release production boards are expected to ship with the fixed MAX10 image. Early production MDKs may) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 85.30 Td (  need reflashing.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 63.70 Td (Q13. What should be debugged first if a customer says the demo does not) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 500 26 Td (Page 17 of 19) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
