endobj
40 0 obj
<< /Length 3500 >>
stream
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 746.00 Td (work?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 719.20 Td (Debug in this order:) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 697.60 Td (1. FPGA programmed with correct SOF.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 686.80 Td (2. Thor in correct 10G or 25G mode.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 676.00 Td (3. ethtool link detected.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 665.20 Td (4. ping 192.168.0.2.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 654.40 Td (5. hololink-enumerate.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 643.60 Td (6. Camera I2C configuration.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 632.80 Td (7. Display/X11.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 622.00 Td (8. AI model or TensorRT engine.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 600.40 Td (Q14. What does `hololink-enumerate` prove?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 573.60 Td (It proves that the host can discover the HSB endpoint over Ethernet and read board metadata. It does not prove) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 562.80 Td (  camera power or camera I2C.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 541.20 Td (Q15. Why is `--cam 8` not always correct?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 514.40 Td (The 25G Group A design can expose eight logical streams/SIFs, but the physical board may only have two cameras) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 503.60 Td (  installed. For two physical cameras, use --cam 2. Use --cam 8 only when the replicated-stream demo is intended) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 492.80 Td (  and validated.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 471.20 Td (Q16. Why does 25G use more FPGA resources?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 444.40 Td (The CoE packetizer logic is enabled per SIF. In this design it adds approximately 7k ALMs per SIF. With eight) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 433.60 Td (  SIFs, this significantly increases resource utilization.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 412.00 Td (Q17. What is the 25G repeated-run workaround?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 385.20 Td (Before every 25G CoE run after the first, refresh the interface:) Tj ET
BT /F3 7.5 Tf 50 363.60 Td (sudo ip link set mgbe0_0 down ; sudo ip link set mgbe0_0 up) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 343.70 Td (This resets the MGBE interface state and avoids repeated-run CoE instability observed on AGX Thor.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 322.10 Td (Q18. Should customers use 10G or 25G?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 295.30 Td (For first evaluation and maximum stability, start with 10G. For bandwidth or 25G-specific demonstrations, use) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 284.50 Td (  25G with CoE mode and the MGBE refresh workaround.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 262.90 Td (Q19. Why do GUI failures happen inside Docker?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 236.10 Td (Holoviz requires access to the host display. If X11 permissions or XDG_RUNTIME_DIR are missing, the pipeline) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 225.30 Td (  may run but the visualizer fails. Use xhost on the host and set XDG_RUNTIME_DIR inside the container.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 203.70 Td (Q20. Why does PeopleNet take a long time on first run?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 176.90 Td (The first run builds a TensorRT engine from the ONNX model. This can take several minutes. The engine is) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 166.10 Td (  cached, so later runs start faster.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 144.50 Td (Q21. Why did PeopleNet crash in InferenceOp?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 117.70 Td (The AGX5 script had metadata enabled. NVIDIA documentation notes an open metadata issue with InferenceOp.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 106.90 Td (  Setting self.is_metadata_enabled = False resolved the runtime crash.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 50 85.30 Td (Q22. What is the best customer demo order?) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.8 Tf 50 58.50 Td (Recommended order:) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 500 26 Td (Page 18 of 19) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
